| Symbol | Meaning | First seen |
|--------|---------|-----------|
| `Σᵢ xᵢ`, `xᵢ`, `n` | Sum, indexing, count | 00 |
| `W ∈ ℝ^{V×d}`, `W[i]` | Matrix shape, row lookup | 01 |
| `μ, σ², ε` | Mean, variance, epsilon | 02 |
| `γ, β` | Learnable scale and shift | 02 |
| `Q, K, V`, `d_k`, `softmax`, `^T` | Attention | 03 |
| `GELU`, `Φ`, `erf` | Activation | 05 |
| `x_{l+1} = x_l + F(x_l)` | Residual connection | 06 |
| `W_E^T` | Weight-tied projection | 07 |
| `L`, `log`, `P(y\|x)` | Loss, log, conditional prob | 08 |
| `α`, `β₁/β₂`, `∇`, `θ`, `λ` | Optimizer symbols | 09 |
| `T` | Temperature | 12 |
| `RMS(x)` | Root mean square | 16 |
| `θᵢ`, `R(θ)` | RoPE frequencies, rotation | 17 |

</details>

## Key Concepts

| Concept | What it means |
|---------|--------------|
| **RoPE** | Rotary Position Embeddings — encode position by rotating Q and K. Jianlin Su, April 2021. |
| **Inverse frequency** | `θᵢ = 1/(base^(2i/d))` — low channels rotate fast, high channels rotate slow |
| **Relative positions** | RoPE makes dot(Q, K) depend only on position *difference*, not absolute positions |
| **Base** | Controls the frequency spectrum — 10000 is standard, too small = positions blur together |
| **No ceiling** | Unlike learned embeddings, RoPE can handle any sequence length |
